# No Cursor attribution

Never add any Cursor attribution to git commits, pull requests, or code comments. This includes:

- `Co-authored-by: Cursor <cursoragent@cursor.com>`
- `Made-with: Cursor` or similar commit trailers
- `--trailer` flags that inject Cursor attribution
- PR descriptions or comments crediting Cursor

When creating commits, use only the user's subject and body. If attribution was added by the environment, amend or rebase to remove it before pushing.
